Subject: Related party disclosures — LJM structures

Board members,

I want to briefly address the LJM Cayman and LJM2 Co-Investment partnerships
managed by our CFO Andrew Fastow.

The Audit Committee has reviewed the structures and is satisfied that the
transactions are conducted at arm's length. The Chewco and JEDI vehicles
serve a legitimate business purpose in managing our merchant investment portfolio.

Ben Glisan and Richard Causey have confirmed the accounting treatment is
consistent with GAAP. Our external auditors have signed off.

I have full confidence in Andy Fastow's management of these partnerships.

Kenneth Lay
Chairman & CEO, Enron Corp
